    {
      "sort": 500000,
      "name": "Family Rolls",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "PzONb0J36K4pjM49",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>This is an automated process.</p><p>There are two parts to this stage</p><p><strong>Family Survival</strong></p><p>A dice roll is made for all children up to the age of five. The outcome is shown in a chat card. Where a child dies the relevant family member item is updated to show the death.</p><p><strong>Childbirth</strong></p><p>The first question is who is testing for childbirth. If there is no test to be done then select \"none\". If your character can bear a child then select \"Self\". If your spouse is the target of your affections then select \"Spouse\" otherwise if it is a lover select \"Other\".</p><p>If you have unspent Prestige points you will have the option to spend them.</p><p>You will then be asked to enter some relevant information, what you are asked will depend on who the person who may get pregnant is and your circumstances.</p><p>Dice are rolled and the outcome appears on the chat card.</p><p>You may, if you have chosen to spend Prestige, be asked about the gender of the child(ren). In the event of a Tragedy you may be asked if a midwife is available to help prevent death.</p><p>All children (whether they survive or not) are added to the family on the @UUID[Compendium.Pendragon.instructions.JournalEntry.b5d7Ha8LOeLSNvul.JournalEntryPage.fRLDTfqAgmiltXyr]{House Tab}</p><p>If the marriage turns out to be barren then either the Spouse family member is updated or you are. No adjustments made if the person who may have conceived was \"other\"</p>"
      },
